  saturated fat: 33 g
  carbohydrates: 93 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1440 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
---

Bring a #large pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce (except
@broccoli rice{6%oz}).

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking
water, then drain.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pot over medium heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}
and 1 tbsp scallion greens; toast, stirring, until panko is golden,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pot.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pot over medium-high heat. Add broccoli rice,
scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook,
stirring, until broccoli is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and 1/2 cup reserved
pasta cooking water; bring to a simmer.

> 3 cups water works best for 2 servings. Use 4 cups for 4 servings.

Stir in @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @cheddar cheese{1%cup},
and @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cheeses
melt and sauce is thick and creamy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained cavatappi; stir until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until
> pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Remove from heat.

Divide mac and cheese between bowls. Garnish with toasted panko and remaining
scallion greens. Serve.